article.headline: N. Arizona 91, Bethany, Calif. 50
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Cameron Jones scored 20 points and Northern Arizona shot a season-high 57.4 percent in a 91-50 victory over Bethany (Calif.) on Saturday night. Josh Lepley had 15 points and Austin Smith 12 for the Lumberjacks (6-2), who won their sixth straight. Kenny Thompson scored 17 points for the Bruins (0-9), an NAIA school who shot just 32.1 percent en route to their 19th straight loss dating to last season. The Lumberjacks took advantage of a distinct size advantage, outscoring Bethany 62-16 in the paint. Northern Arizona also had a 19-0 edge in fast-break points. A 24-5 run over a six-minute span gave the Lumberjacks a 47-26 lead at halftime. Shane Johannsen had 11 points for the Lumberjacks.
